      "created_at": "2022-01-05T07:20:22.946Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Welcome Berto, and I would say more than 70% of our users are not native English speakers so you are not alone <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>\n<p>Your English is fine and the answer is yes and yes.  You need to change the setting in the app from resistance mode to slope mode.</p>\n<p>And yes if you upload GPX it will convert to slopes but you will also see previous watts you did too so you can decide to if you want to try to hit the same targets but really watts target and slope are not related.  Meaning you can have low watts going uphill or high watts going uphill.  Without visual stimulation like Zwift, RTG or sometihng automatic slope mode is a different experience in our app than those.</p>",
